<br>
And yes.. Im getting in trouble in EQ for not being around.. but it is so much more relaxing to be able to pop into the game.. do a some hunting or shopping and pop back out. A group isnt 'dependent' on your being in it. But if you show up.. everybody is happy cause that just means what you are doing is different. The game isnt dependent (so far at our levels that I can tell) on a certain type of profession being there. Just changes the parameters on what you do. <br>
<br>
Guess you could say Im hooked.. I still like EQ, but if given a choice right now.. I would go with AO .. just a lot more casual gamer friendly. <br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
Deirdra <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ukrystl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krystl</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(8/14/01 11:16:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=630.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: some Ramblings</span><hr size=1> Woo hoo!  I love to read a post like that, D : )  I am truly hooked on AO here too, obviously.  At this point, I am carrying all THREE games still - EQ, AC and AO.  Tomorrow night, I am passing some items to an old friend in EQ, then I will be turning my account over to Justin (Airrlan).  I might still play EQ (He's retaining my password and all), but it won't really be MY character, it will be his - which is fine - I really do not have this much time!  LOL<br>
<br>
I have to admit, I really like the social/independent mixture I find in AO.  When I log in, I try to find out what everyone is up to.  I think my favorite is when a bunch of us join up and beat the tar out of those deep reds, but it's also great to pull a 'normal' mission and run it with just a friend or two.  Even when I log on, and noone is around (or, I suppose if I ever feel anti-social, but I'm not sure I know what that is &lt;grins&gt;) I can run around and shop or do the auction thing or attempt to do a mission solo.  That is all just with my main char.  It's hard to find time to do much with any of my 'younger' ones! : )<br>
<br>
Needless to say, there is no easy way to keep up with three games.  EQ is in my past, and I'm sure AC will be soon also.  I have great things to say about all of them, but as we all know, it all boils down to the people.  AO blows the others away in gameplay!  Hahahaha!!!!<br>
<br>
&lt;hugs FTFL&gt;<br>
Krystl<br>
