<br>
As you can probably tell, we're having a lot of fun in Rubi-Ka, but we can't wait until you and Dia finally get here! There's still a lot of annoying bugs, but judging from the amount of hours everyone seems to be playing, the general consensus seems to be that the gameplay more than makes up for it. <br>
<br>
There's just so much stuff to see and do. The mission system makes it easy to set up a challenging (sometimes a bit too challenging!) fight no matter how many people are available. Equipment is very important, so you can spend a lot of time shopping, either visiting the various stores (I can count at least 12 basic general stores in Omni territory alone, each of which has a randomly changing inventory), or hanging around in towns and listening to the player auctions. There's implants to decide on, and then you have to find the components to build them, and possibly someone to assemble them for you if your skill isn't high enough. And the eye candy is just amazing, just about every night I see something that makes me stop and say &quot;wow!&quot; <br>
<br>
It looks like it's going to get even more interesting in the next few weeks as the story line starts up. Like D said in her other post, they had their first test of the event system they're going to use last night. Godzilla-sized spiders attacked a major Clan town, and there was a huge battle to defend the town. No one had ever seen monsters anywhere near that big on Rubi-Ka before, and everyone who was there said it was a complete blast.<br>
<br>
